Ten licensing officials have been arrested at Malamulele and Mutale testing stations in Limpopo for allegedly selling drivers licenses. The suspects allegedly sold driving licenses to applicants for R8 000. Hawks provincial spokesperson, Matimba Maluleke says the suspects include examiners and instructors. “Following a community outcry since 2017 we embarked on a project driven operation aimed at addressing allegations of of corrupt activities at the testing stations in the province; the suspects include a senior licensing officer, three examiners, tow clerks, cashiers, instructor, general workers and a middle man are expected to appear at the Malamulele and Mutale Magistrate’s Court on Friday.” 